                            <comment id="17450" author="robh" created="Tue, 2 May 2006 01:26:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chris,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I posted a more detailed description of why this change was necessary on &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1951&quot; title=&quot;NameMatchMethodPointcutAdvisor in CVS does not match M4 distribution&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-1951&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-1951&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. For your use case I would recommend either using the newly reintroduced setClassFilter method or more preferably using a custom implementation of TransactionAttributeSource which should have the desired effect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hope that helps.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;/p&gt;

